EXPLORING DEPLOYMENT AND INFRASTRUCTURE MANAGEMENT SERVICES

  This services help you quickly stand up new applications, automate the management of infrastructure, and provide real-time visibility into system health

Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
  Allows you to write a script to provision AWS resources. The benefit is that you provision resouces in a reproducible manner that saves time.

  ex:

    json:

      "MyBucket":{
        "Type":"AWS::S3::Bucket"
      }

    YAML:

      MyBucket:
        Type:AWS::S3::Bucket

CloudFormation 
  Allows you to provision AWS resources using Infrastructure as Code (IaC).

  Provides a repeatable process for provisioning resources
  Works w/ most AWS services
  Creates templates for the resources you want to provision

  Ex:
    Automate the infrastructure-provisioning process 4 EC2 servers.
    U can use CloudFormation to automate the creation of EC2 instances in you AWS account.

Elastic Beanstalk

  Allows you to deploy your web application and web services to AWS.
  Orchestration service that provision resources 
  Automatically handles the deployment
  Monitors application healh via a health dashboard
  
  ex:
    It can deploy, handle capacity provisioning, load balacing, and Auto Scaling. It also can monitors the health of your application.

OpsWorks
  Deploy code and mange application 
  Manage on-premises servers or EC2 instances in AWS Cloud.
  Workds w/ Chef and Puppet automation platforms
  
  ex:
    Allows you to define software installation scripts and automate configuration for your application servers.
